```class Solution {
    public String removeOccurrences(String s, String part) {
        while (s.contains(part)) {
            s = s.substring(0, s.indexOf(part)) + s.substring(s.indexOf(part) + part.length());
        }
        return s;
    }
}```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n*m)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses a while loop to continuously remove the substring part from the string s until all occurrences are removed. The substring method is used to remove the part from the string, and the contains method is used to check if the part is still present in the string. The time complexity is O(n*m) because in the worst case, we might have to traverse the entire string for each occurrence of the part. The space complexity is O(1) because we are not using any extra space that scales with the input size.

